  <scopecontent id="aspace_29e6cc6e1b133b51842032117ae2589f">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Accounts of W.P.F.B. Pomeroy, an Ovid cabinet maker (1838-1856) and Rockwell Manning, a hosteler (1829-1835). In the Manning ledger are notes of Laverne Blackwell, a child, on curing horses and penmanship practice exercises.</p>  </scopecontent>
