  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_5b54f6e3e199daa7f1731cac6624b31d" level="item"><did><unittitle>W.P.F.B. Pomeroy, Ovid, N.Y.,</unittitle><unitid>Item #1</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1838-05-14/1856-01-10" type="inclusive">May 14, 1838 - January 10, 1856.</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ee1e306ac7999b5e0d5a8e2b3c404ca6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Contains accounts of a cabinent and coffin maker.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_6708ae7fc51fc11df0ceefa6c00c5a3d" level="item"><did><unittitle>Rockwell Manning ledger,</unittitle><unitid>Item #2</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1829-08-29/1835-06-19" type="inclusive">August 29, 1829 - June 19, 1835.</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_8e095a2c58678c09218212e2d42dfc73"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Accounts of a hosteler. Mixed vith the accounts are the notes of Laverne Blackvell - a child, who used the volume to practice penmanship, keep notes on curing horses, and take down a recipe for invisible ink.</p></scopecontent></c01></dsc>
